With our input text safely converted into a base-10 integer inside the guess variable, we route our execution path through a series of logical validation forks.
While the fundamental logic matches Python, JavaScript uses standard brackets () to hold conditions, curly braces {} to wrap code blocks, and the logical OR operator ||:
// Give a hint using if / else if / else.
if (guess < 1 || guess > 20) {
console.log(“That number is out of range. Try again.”);
} else if (guess < secret) {
console.log(“Too low, try again.”);
} else if (guess > secret) {
console.log(“Too high, try again.”);
} else {
console.log(“You got it in”, tries, “tries!”);
}Guided Walkthrough: Auditing Single-Chance Branch Logic
